##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("LimitedNumeric");

$a=random(5,10,1);
$b=random(1,$a-2,1);
$c=random(2,5,1);

$ans=Compute(($a-$b)*$c);


##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Evaluate the expression:

    [`` ([$a]-[$b])[$c]=  ``]  [________]{$ans} 

END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

Since there is no operation symbol between [`([$a]-[$b])`] and [`[$c]`], it implies multiplication.

We need to perform operations inside the parentheses first, as parentheses have a higher priority than multiplication.

      [``
        \begin{aligned}[t]
           ([$a]-[$b])[$c] & = ([$a-$b])[$c] \\
                                 & =  [$ans] 
          \end{aligned}
      ``]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();


